28/10/2005
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Jonathan Scheele, head of the EC delegation in Romania, expressed disappointment Thursday (27 October) over the Romanian Senate's rejection of the draft law on the status of minorities. Romania should quickly resolve problems flagged in the recent EC monitoring report, he said.
In other news, Romania takes over the rotating chairmanship of the Black Sea Economic Co-operation organisation on Friday. Foreign ministers of the member states are meeting to discuss priorities in the year ahead. 
Also Friday, the Romanian government announced that a new case of bird flu has been discovered in the country's northeast. Agriculture Minister Gheorghe Flutur said British scientists found the H5N1 virus in samples from a dead heron. (AFP - 28/10/05; Rompres - 27/10/05)
